%T A394379 69,35,75,55,65,88,85,29,56,95,24,104,31,87,48,115,93,96,64,7,120,35,
%U A394379 784,35,145,37,136,105,155,77,91,119,168,133,111,16,161,41,152,175
%N A394379 a(n) is the distance between circumcenter O and centroid G of the triangle (A394102(n), A394101(n), A394100(n)).
%C A394379 On the Euler line, the centroid G divides the segment OH in the ratio 2 : 1, with OG : GH : OH = 1 : 2 : 3. Consequently, GH = 2*a(n) and OH = 3*a(n).
%H A394379 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euler_line">Euler line</a>
%e A394379 a(1) = 0 because for the triangle (x, y, z) = (1, 1, 1) we have OG = 0.
%e A394379 a(2) = 1 because for the triangle (x, y, z) = (5, 7, 8) we have OG = 1.
%e A394379 a(3) = 5 because for the triangle (x, y, z) = (7, 8, 13) we have OG = 5.
%p A394379 # See Huber link in A394376.
